race.comment: Competitive race but fancy CAVERN (8) can measure up off the maiden win on debut where he won well at Bendigo over 1000m after showing early speed. Straight to a BM62 on a Wednesday but he looks smart and should take beating with natural improvement. CLOSE TO MIDNIGHT (3) resumes. His form last time in reads very well for this, with close-up finishes behind some well-performed types. He's won a trial leading in and should go close. IMMINANCE (7) can mix her form but did win well last time at Sale and a repeat of that effort would see her in the finish. MARILYN'S EDGE (9) is going okay and an each-way hope.
